Binary output issue
* Please change the output requirements so that there are more than 2 possible answers in total. According to the contribution guidelines, binary output should be avoided in clashes.

All sections
* Please format "YES" and "NO" as {{constants}} and delete the quotation marks.

* Please format all variables using [[this_syntax]].

Input section
* Please delete the example (an example is shown in Example section).

* Please write one description per line using this format:

<<Line ?>>: variable_type [[variable_name]] variable_description
e.g.
<<Line 1>>: An integer [[P]] for the pay per hour

Thanks.
i fixed it, sorry about that. i didn't know how to format all that stuff or that there was an example included, or that binary output wasn't allowed. thanks for the information!

No worries.

Would you please follow up the comments below on the revised version?

Input section
* Please format all line numbers in <<bold>> (the same way you did in Output section).

* Please include variable types in all lines, e.g. "An integer [[P]]" instead of just "[[P]]".

Cases
* Please swap the last test and the last validator so that there is at least one validator which requires the output of YES.

Thanks.
Ok, revised! Thank you for your help!
